OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,FProposals to move away from "blanket"
OL,7,Fone-to-one classroom support for
OL,8,Fchildren with special educational
OL,9,Fneeds (SEN) in Northern Ireland have
OL,10,Fbeen published.
OL,12,FThe Education Authority (EA) said the
OL,13,F"current rigid approaches" in schools
OL,14,Foften do not work for children.
OL,16,FCurrently, the large majority of
OL,17,Fchildren with SEN statements in
OL,18,FNorthern Ireland have access to one-to-
OL,19,Fone support from a classroom assistant.
OL,26,@nD@]OUnD@eO]uD@AOUuD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,FThe EA, which manages school services
OL,7,Fin the region, has said every child
OL,8,Fwho requires one-to-one support will
OL,9,Fcontinue to receive it but added there
OL,10,Fare concerns the current model can
OL,11,Fisolate some children.
OL,13,FIt has launched an eight-week public
OL,14,Fconsultation which would mean schools
OL,15,Fwill have "more flexibility on how to
OL,16,Fbest provide support".
OL,26,@wD@KOUxD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,FEA chief transformation officer, Tomas
OL,7,FAdell said: "The evidence, both in
OL,8,FNorthern Ireland, and from best
OL,9,Fpractice elsewhere is clear: each day
OL,10,Fthat we continue to operate the
OL,11,Fcurrent support model for our children
OL,12,Fand young people with SEN, we accept
OL,13,Fless than optimal provision for their
OL,14,Fneeds.
OL,16,F"To improve outcomes, it is essential
OL,17,Fto that we transform and update the
OL,18,Fcurrent model of support.
OL,26,@oD@MOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,F"Reform can also bring benefits for
OL,7,Fclassroom assistants, teachers and
OL,8,Fschool communities as a whole."
OL,10,FThe proposals include allowing schools
OL,11,Fto move away from the "current one-
OL,12,Fsize-fits-all model with its over-
OL,13,Freliance on one-to-one classroom
OL,14,Fassistant support for all children".
OL,16,FAn EA statement said: "Every child who
OL,17,Fneeds one-to-one support will continue
OL,18,Fto receive it.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@_O]sD@WOUvD@cO]xD@WOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,F"Any changes will be introduced
OL,7,Fsensitively on an individual basis,
OL,8,Fthrough the established annual review
OL,9,Fprocess for each child's provision.
OL,11,F"The current classroom support model
OL,12,Fcannot properly deliver for children
OL,13,For meet increasing levels of need.
OL,15,F"Faced with this reality, many schools
OL,16,Fin Northern Ireland have begun to
OL,17,Fdevelop alternative approaches to
OL,18,Fclassroom support.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,F"The reforms set out in the public
OL,7,Fconsultation will help formalise and
OL,8,Fencourage this approach."
OL,10,FThe EA said alternatives to a "blanket
OL,11,Fone-to-one support model" would
OL,12,Finclude small group learning sessions,
OL,13,Fuse of different teaching methods, and
OL,14,Fenhanced access to educational and
OL,15,Fhealth specialists.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@YO]rD@_OUsD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,FIt said that planned reforms would be
OL,7,Fimplemented gradually over a number of
OL,8,Fyears and will be shaped by input from
OL,9,Fchildren, parents, carers, teachers,
OL,10,Fclassroom assistants and school
OL,11,Fleaders.
OL,13,FThe EA said: "The reforms will involve
OL,14,Fchanges to the process for new
OL,15,Fstatements of special educational need.
OL,17,F"Reflecting the more flexible support
OL,18,Fmodel, new statements will be focused
OL,19,Fon the individual needs of each child
OL,20,Fand will not be overly prescriptive on
OL,21,Fclassroom support options."
OL,26,@uD@NOUyD@AOU}D@[O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774375556
OL,3,C'Current rigid approaches' in schools
OL,4,Ccould isolate SEN children
OL,6,FThe consultation proposes that
OL,7,Fimplementation of the new classroom
OL,8,Fsupport model will start from
OL,9,FSeptember.
OL,11,FThe EA said it will begin by working
OL,12,Fwith around 150 mainstream schools and
OL,13,F40 special schools in Northern Ireland.
OL,15,FIn 2027-2028, rollout will cover
OL,16,Fschools across two health and social
OL,17,Fcare trust areas and will extend to
OL,18,Fremaining areas in 2028-29.
OL,20,FCatch up with the latest UTV Live on
OL,21,FITVX
